<paragraph id="3449FD08DB2BFFD08CD3994B40D8FE0B" blockId="4.[151,1436,1729,2006]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,429]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="526" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB2BFFD18CD3994B4433F8E3" bold="true" box="[199,1073,1836,1861]" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">
Morphological characters of relevance for the study of 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB2BFFD18F9B994B4428F8E3" authorityName="Ogloblin" authorityYear="1948" box="[911,1066,1836,1861]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB2BFFD18F9B994B4428F8E3" bold="true" box="[911,1066,1836,1861]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Tetraglossula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Bees of this genus have two submarginal cells (Ogloblin 1948, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2BFFD18E3899364273F8CF" box="[556,625,1873,1898]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1332,1354]" captionTargetBox="[235,1361,398,1290]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[190,1397,375,1309]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 3. Allotype (♀) of Leioproctus (Tetraglossula) anthracinus Michener, 1989 [SEMC]: (A) lateral habitus; (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) mesosoma, dorsal view; (E) metasoma, dorsal view; (F) labels attached to the specimen. Ownership rights to these images and their copyright belong to SEMC (Snow Entomological Museum Collection). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841532/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
) and body length varies from 
<quantity id="F30E50EDDB2BFFD18FC99936446FF8CF" box="[989,1133,1873,1898]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="6.0">6 to 12 mm</quantity>
; these bees are slender in comparison to other neopasiphaeine bees with similar length. 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB2BFFD18F4B991243F4F828" authorityName="Ogloblin" authorityYear="1948" box="[863,1014,1909,1934]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB2BFFD18F4B991243F4F828" box="[863,1014,1909,1934]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">Tetraglossula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are morphologically similar, although superficially diverse (Michener 1989, 695), pubescence varying from black or fuscous to light grey, and the integument varying from completely black to bright orange or red on the metasoma of 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB2BFFD1888899D94503F873" authorityName="Michener" authorityYear="1989" box="[1180,1281,1981,2005]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fucosa">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB2BFFD1888899D94503F873" box="[1180,1281,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">T. fucosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB2BFFD1892E99D94596F870" authority="Almeida &amp; Gibran, 2017" authorityName="Almeida &amp; Gibran" authorityYear="2017" box="[1338,1428,1981,2006]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="525" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meloi" status="sp.n.">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB2BFFD1892E99D94596F870" box="[1338,1428,1981,2006]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="525">T. meloi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="1DB19C61DB2AFFD08C839EF040CCFF16" box="[151,206,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" rank="species">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB2AFFD08C839EF040CCFF16" bold="true" box="[151,206,151,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">sp.n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Male genitalia and sterna VI–VIII (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08E7B9EF042CAFF16" box="[623,712,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08EC29EF042F1FF16" box="[726,755,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1098,1120]" captionTargetBox="[197,1403,208,1073]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1420,193,1092]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 15. Male genitalia of Tetraglossula spp.: dorsal, ventral, and lateral views: (A – C) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (D – F) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (G – I) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (J – L) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (M – O) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841556/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">15</figureCitation>
) overall similar, although continuous shape variation of S6 among the species of 
<taxonomicName id="F3F6868BDB2AFFD08D9E9EDB4223FF73" authorityName="Ogloblin" authorityYear="1948" box="[394,545,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Tetraglossula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0682211ADB2AFFD08D9E9EDB4223FF73" box="[394,545,188,213]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Tetraglossula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be noticed (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08ECE9EDB432FFF72" box="[730,813,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
); the curvature of the apical process of S 
<quantity id="F30E50EDDB2AFFD088EC9EDB4521FF73" box="[1272,1315,188,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="5" pageNumber="526" unit="in" value="8.0">8 in</quantity>
relation to its disc, as well as the shapes of the S8 lateral process, spiculum, and apodemes also exhibit interspecific variation (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08C8B9F6340F0FEBA" box="[159,242,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Even though S6 and S 
<date id="4048DBC8DB2AFFD08DEB9F634241FEBB" box="[511,579,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">8 may</date>
reveal differences among species, those dissimilarities are difficult to define and there seems to be some level on intraspecific variation too. Consistent species delimitation and determination can be most reliably done comparing two features of male S7 (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08F719F2B43B9FEC2" box="[869,955,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1853,1875]" captionTargetBox="[321,1294,554,1804]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[274,1325,517,1845]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 14. Male metasomal sterna VI (ventral view), VII (dorsal view), and VIII (dorsal and lateral views) of Tetraglossula spp.: (A – D) T. anthracina (Michener) [specimen from Brazil, MG, Santana do Riacho-UFMG IHY- 4683]; (E – H) T. bigamica (Strand) [specimen from Brazil, RS, Rosário do Sul-RPSP- 162186]; (I – L) T. deltivaga Ogloblin [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto- RPSP]; (M – P) T. fucosa (Michener) [Brazil, SP, Ribeirão Preto-RPSP]; (R – U) T. meloi Almeida &amp; Gibran, sp. n. [Holotype, RPSP  951577]. ALb, apical lobe of S 7; BLb, basal lobe of S 7; LLb, lateral lobe of S 7; LPr, lateral process of S 8; MPr, median process of S 8; scale bars = 0.2 mm. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841554/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
): (a) the shape and relative position of the basal lobe of S7; and (b) the shape of the medial sclerotized region positioned proximally to the apical and basal lobes.
</paragraph>
