<paragraph id="3449FD08DB2AFFD38CD398C24134FE21" blockId="5.[151,1437,1700,2013]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,392]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="527" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">
Most of the following additional diagnostic characters for the genus were extracted from Michener (1989, 654–656; for the complete set of characters used to compare the various taxa of Neopasiphaeinae, refer to that work): glossa deeply bifid, lobes acute (
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08E4A988B42A1F8A3" box="[606,675,1772,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1435,1457]" captionTargetBox="[263,1327,723,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[259,1328,700,1412]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Head and mouthparts of Tetraglossula anthracina (Michener, 1989): (A) frontal view of male [Sabará-Brazil, UFMG- 460]; (B) lateral view of labium of female [Santana do Riacho-Brazil-RPSP]. Scale bars = 1.0 mm. ACT = anterior conjunctival thickening; Ga = galea; Gl = glossa; LbP = labial palpus; Md = mandible; MxP = maxillary palpus; PGl = paraglossa; Ppg = palpiger; Prm = prementum; Sbm = submentum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841528/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
; Ogloblin 1948, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08F71988B43A8F8A3" box="[869,938,1772,1797]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1253,1275]" captionTargetBox="[221,1355,216,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[198,1388,193,1231]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Holotype (♀) of Bicolletes sitgmatica Strand, 1910 [ZMB]: (A) lateral habitus (scale bar = 1.0 mm); (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) metasoma, dorsal view; (E) labels attached to the specimen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841544/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), 7–10× longer than proximal width. Labial palpus ordinary (Ogloblin 1948, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08E139977424AF88F" box="[519,584,1808,1833]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1435,1457]" captionTargetBox="[263,1327,723,1406]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[259,1328,700,1412]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Head and mouthparts of Tetraglossula anthracina (Michener, 1989): (A) frontal view of male [Sabará-Brazil, UFMG- 460]; (B) lateral view of labium of female [Santana do Riacho-Brazil-RPSP]. Scale bars = 1.0 mm. ACT = anterior conjunctival thickening; Ga = galea; Gl = glossa; LbP = labial palpus; Md = mandible; MxP = maxillary palpus; PGl = paraglossa; Ppg = palpiger; Prm = prementum; Sbm = submentum." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841528/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); maxillary palpus long, last or last two palpomeres extending beyond apex of galea (Ogloblin 1948, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08DAF99534202F8EB" box="[443,512,1844,1869]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1253,1275]" captionTargetBox="[221,1355,216,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[198,1388,193,1231]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 9. Holotype (♀) of Bicolletes sitgmatica Strand, 1910 [ZMB]: (A) lateral habitus (scale bar = 1.0 mm); (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) metasoma, dorsal view; (E) labels attached to the specimen." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841544/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Labrum about 6× as wide as long; labral apico-lateral lobes weak in the male, conspicuous and serrate or pectinate in the female (Michener 1989, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08F89993F43EEF8D7" box="[925,1004,1880,1905]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[222,1356,971,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[204,1383,951,1902]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Tetraglossula deltivaga Ogloblin, 1948, ♀, Ribeirão Preto, São Paulo, Brazil [RPSP- 121831]: (A) lateral habitus; (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) metasoma, dorsal view; (E) labels attached to the specimen. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
G,H). Apical margin of the clypeus of the male is a small median lobe overhanging the labrum. Inner orbits not or very slightly converging below, almost without concave region. Mandible slender in female (Michener 1989, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08FC899C74430F81F" box="[988,1074,1952,1977]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[222,1356,971,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[204,1383,951,1902]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Tetraglossula deltivaga Ogloblin, 1948, ♀, Ribeirão Preto, São Paulo, Brazil [RPSP- 121831]: (A) lateral habitus; (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) metasoma, dorsal view; (E) labels attached to the specimen. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
J), simple and slender in male (Ogloblin 1948, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08D4699A34194F87B" box="[338,406,1988,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1985,2007]" captionTargetBox="[242,1339,1107,1942]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[223,1375,1087,1979]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 8. Holotype (♂) of Bicolletes bigamica Strand, 1910 [ZMB]: (A) lateral habitus; (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) labels attached to the specimen. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841542/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
; Michener 1989, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB2AFFD08E4A99A342ACF87B" box="[606,686,1988,2013]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1924,1946]" captionTargetBox="[222,1356,971,1883]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[204,1383,951,1902]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 13. Tetraglossula deltivaga Ogloblin, 1948, ♀, Ribeirão Preto, São Paulo, Brazil [RPSP- 121831]: (A) lateral habitus; (B) dorsal habitus; (C) frontal view; (D) metasoma, dorsal view; (E) labels attached to the specimen. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841552/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="526">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
K). Facial fovea shallowly impressed. Ocelli in front of summit of vertex; vertex convex and rounded behind ocelli. Jugal lobe exceeding level of 
<emphasis id="0682211ADB29FFD3880F9EFE444BFF16" box="[1051,1097,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">cu-v</emphasis>
. Metapostnotum smooth with marginal groove strongly pitted, basal sub-horizontal zone sloping, about as long as metanotum or shorter. Hind tibial inner spur straight or gently curved; inner margin pectinate (Ogloblin 1948, 
<figureCitation id="ACCDE18DDB29FFD3885B9EB84494FF5E" box="[1103,1174,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1542,1564]" captionTargetBox="[234,1363,508,1491]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[193,1394,481,1520]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Holotype (♂) of Leioproctus (Tetraglossula) fucosus Michener, 1989 [SEMC]: (A) lateral habitus; (B) dorsal habitus; (C) labels attached to the specimen; (D) frontal view; (E) mesosoma, dorsal view; (F) metasoma, dorsal view. Ownership rights to these images and their copyright belong to SEMC (Snow Entomological Museum Collection). Scale bars = 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/841534/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); outer margin serrate, similarly to both margins of outer spur. Scopa on tibia, femur, and distal part of trochanter of sparse simple setae (if plumose, setae with 2–5 branches). The metasomal tergal setal bands absent or weak; metasomal scopa (S2–S5) dense, formed by yellow simple setae. T7 of the male has a triangular, bare pygidial plate, tapering to a narrow rounded apex.
</paragraph>
